&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp i am sitting at a head of a master table. twin cream candles burn with a deviant grin at the base of a tall, slender and clear vase of dead red roses near the midsection of the table. atop a fading oak floor and then a furrowed red rug with golden fringe are four dark and ornate chairs with vivid violet cushions. the legs of the chairs are worn smooth and join the bloodsoaked carpet in dragon's talons clenching small, smooth spheres. i sit in one of these demoniacal thrones with arms splayed straight out in front of me, with my chin resting on my left, atrophied bicep. a tall glass of slender clarity sticks broken into my fingers as i stare at a solemn white feline staring my way at the other end of the vast table. she looks at me with a certain audacity. she casually glances into my deep, locked soul, as so many are able to do so easily; and I erratically discover the meaning of life. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp i am in a forest now. i am on my knees in the midst of a bamboo grove. all about me, bamboo pierces the sky. a light snow has begun to fall eternally. fallen shoots and leaves lay about me as more twirl majestically down from above. a deep blue seeps down between every leaf and every branch, as far as i can see through the misty snow. a full moon radiates above me, shining with a brilliant omniscience through the turmoil prevalent in every direction. i rise to a short hunch, a kind of stoop, and i cherish a small trinket which is unseen within the clutches of my body. i peer in every direction around me, as if i am eagerly looking for something. i glance in every direction several times but never cease to search. i make a pass behind my back and to my right and i see what my heart desired. a tall, slender girl is standing beside a bamboo tree, grasping it with her right hand. her hair is dark, long and is floating in the wind with a calm sublimity as if everything were beneath the waves. her deep, beautiful eyes contain the sadness of the world, but with a thirst for life which is subtle, and has been all but forgotten by everyone else. she peers at me with a faint allure which she knows i cannot resist. i lift my right leg from its cringed angle below me and take a step. my head is still turned to face her, but i move slowly away, never blinking. i take a slow crescent path through the fallen leaves and approach her from the side, forever will i be lost in her. the snow has begun to fall faster now, with an almost certain ache to leave the heavens from whence it came. still i cling to a small, unseen treasure. i am close now, just in front of her, with my frosted hands held tightly closed between us. i shake her gaze and stare at my sealed hands, and she does the same. i remove a finger and there is darkness within my hands. slowly, i crack my frozen fingers apart and reveal a warm, beating heart.<br>
